href="erct-0023.xml"
title="Path object structure on sections"
addr="erct-0023"
type="local">univalence principle for sections</fr:link>.</fr:p>

 <fr:p>To show that the type of <fr:link
href="erct-000Y.xml"
title="Section-retraction pair"
addr="erct-000Y"
type="local">sections</fr:link> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link
href="erct-001I.xml"
title="Proposition"
addr="erct-001I"
type="local">proposition</fr:link>, we may assume beforehand that we have such a <fr:link
href="erct-000Y.xml"
title="Section-retraction pair"
addr="erct-000Y"
type="local">section</fr:link> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex>; therefore, because we have assumed a <fr:link
href="erct-000Y.xml"
title="Section-retraction pair"
addr="erct-000Y"
type="local">retraction</fr:link> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> already, we know that <fr:tex
